  <datafield tag="545" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Journalist and freelance writer. Showers worked for the New York Times as travel editor and editor of the Sunday Magazine.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The collection includes correspondence; family research and collected family materials, dating back to 1783; personal and professional papers, including biographical material, papers relating to his student years at the University of Michigan, especially concerning activities writing for the Gargoyle;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">papers from his service in the military writing for Yank; writings, published and unpublished; and visual materials. Correspondents include: M. F. K. Fisher, Vladimir Nabokov, Leopold Stokowski, Dorothy Brett, and Ludwig Bemelmans.</subfield>
